SUMMARY:Stella Swings Ella
DESCRIPTION:A swinging tribute to Ella Fitzgerald as Stella Heath brings the First Lady of Song’s jazz legacy to life.\nCelebrate the timeless music of Ella Fitzgerald\, the First Lady of Song\, whose nearly 60-year career helped define American jazz. From her swing-era brilliance at the Savoy Ballroom to her pioneering bebop improvisation and iconic songbook recordings\, Ella’s voice elevated the works of Cole Porter\, Duke Ellington\, and George Gershwin into enduring classics. Her later years saw her captivating audiences worldwide with elegance\, joy\, and unmatched musicality.\nBay Area vocalist Stella Heath\, praised for The Billie Holiday Project and Stella Meets Nat\, takes on Ella’s legendary repertoire in Stella Swings Ella. Backed by an all-star band featuring Ian Scherer (guitar)\, Daniel Fabricant (bass)\, Robby Elfman (saxophone/clarinet)\, and Spike Klein (drums)\, this evening of vintage jazz from the 1930s–1950s promises a vibrant\, soulful tribute to one of music’s greatest voices. \nTICKETS: \nPURCHASE IN ADVANCE AND SAVE!\nZones A & B ensure a seat. Zone C has limited seating\, plus standing room. \nZone A $33\nZone B $28\nZone C $23 (does not guarantee seating)\nTickets at the door $33 (Zone C only) \nDoors open 5:30pm. \nOur kitchen serves our All New Menu from the time doors open until end of intermission. (Kitchen available only at events with 60 or more advance tickets sold)
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/stella-swings-ella/
LOCATION:The California Theatre of Santa Rosa\, 528 7th Street\, Santa Rosa\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Stella.jpg
GEO:38.44252;-122.71621
